  1621→## Types …
  1623→### `P.infer`
  1625→`P.infer<typeof somePattern>` lets you infer a type of value from a type of pattern.
  1626→
  1627→It's particularly useful when validating an API response.
  1628→
  1629→```ts
  1630→const postPattern = {
  1631→  title: P.string,
  1632→  content: P.string,
  1633→  stars: P.number.between(1, 5).optional(),
  1634→  author: {
  1635→    firstName: P.string,
  1636→    lastName: P.string.optional(),
  1637→    followerCount: P.number,
  1638→  },
  1639→} as const;
  1640→
  1641→type Post = P.infer<typeof postPattern>;
  1642→
  1643→// posts: Post[]
  1644→const posts = await fetch(someUrl)
  1645→  .then((res) => res.json())
  1646→  .then((res: unknown): Post[] =>
  1647→    isMatching({ data: P.array(postPattern) }, res) ? res.data : []
  1648→  );
  1649→```
  1650→
